HEADWORD: Subnasal
<hw>Sub*na"sal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>Situated under the nose; <as>as, the <ex>subnasal</ex> point, or
the middle point of the inferior border of the anterior nasal
aperture</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

